Yesterday we said goodbye to River 💔 The most loyal dog I have ever known. River was a foster fail that was so grateful for being rescued and never left my side. She would wait in the window until I got home every day. Sit on the bath mat while I showered. Slept in my room making sure I was always in sight. We all spent the day outside with her and her siblings. We made a circle around her and as difficult as it was to move her back legs, she went up to each of us to nuzzle. She was  surrounded by so much love and went peacefully. She lived to be 15 years old 🙏  I’m grateful she’s at peace and no longer suffering but her absence will no doubt be painful. We love you River 💔 #adoptdontshop

Research indicates that infants, even as young as a few days old, show a preference for attractive faces. 

Studies have demonstrated that newborns spend more time looking at faces deemed attractive by adults, suggesting an innate inclination rather than one developed through socialization.

This preference may be linked to the brain’s affinity for symmetry and average facial features, which are often associated with attractiveness.

Warner Bros. Discovery has announced that its streaming service, currently known as Max, will revert to its former name, HBO Max, starting in summer 2025.

This decision comes after the 2023 rebranding from HBO Max to Max, which aimed to unify content from HBO, Warner Bros., and Discovery networks. 

However, the move led to declining viewer engagement, particularly with 
Discovery’s lifestyle content . By reinstating the HBO branding, the company seeks to emphasize its commitment to high-quality programming and leverage the strong association consumers have with the HBO name.

The rebranding has been acknowledged humorously by the company, with ads stating, “Max is becoming HBO Max!” and referring to the change as “the plot twist everyone’s been waiting for.”

Reverse brainstorming flips the script on traditional problem-solving. Instead of directly seeking solutions, you brainstorm ways to intentionally worsen the problem. This seemingly counterintuitive approach forces you to consider the issue from a different angle. By identifying the worst-case scenarios and why they occur, you uncover unexpected weaknesses that can be addressed. This newfound understanding paves the way for innovative solutions to the original problem.

🧼✨ Your gut is like a dishwasher—and if it doesn’t clean properly, leftover food (aka bacteria) builds up in all the wrong places!  Your Migrating Motor Complex (MMC) is your gut’s built-in cleaning cycle. Every 90-120 minutes between meals, it sweeps out undigested food and bacteria with cleaning waves to keep your small intestine fresh. But if your MMC isn’t working properly (due to stress, infections, or slow motility), bacteria can stick around and overgrow—leading to SIBO or Small Intestinal Bacterial Overgrowth.

If you’re dealing with bloating, diarrhea, constipation, or feeling “backed up” after eating, your gut’s "dishwasher" might not be working properly. 🌀🚫 

✅ The Trio-Smart at-home breath test is the only test that can check for all 3 gases associated with bacterial overgrowth: Hydrogen, Methane, and Hydrogen Sulfide.

✨ DIY Rice Toner for Glowing, Hydrated Skin! ✨
 Gentle, plant-powered care—right from your kitchen shelf 🌾💧
🌿 Ingredients:
½ cup rice (any type you love)
2 tbsp aloe vera gel (fresh or organic)
1 tbsp rosewater (for that soft floral touch)
1 capsule Vitamin E (burst & mix)
🧴 Steps to Follow:
Rinse and soak rice overnight—this releases skin-brightening rice starch.
Strain the rice water in the morning.
Mix aloe vera gel, rosewater, and vitamin E into the rice water.
Pour into a spray bottle, shake well, and refrigerate.

💫 Benefits:
 🌾 Rice Water – Rich in amino acids & ferulic acid; helps brighten and tone skin.
 🌿 Aloe Vera – Soothes irritation, cools, and deeply hydrates.
 🌹 Rosewater – Balances skin pH, reduces redness, and tightens pores.
 💧 Vitamin E – A powerful antioxidant that repairs skin and improves elasticity.
📌 Use it daily to reduce pigmentation, soothe tired skin, and get that dewy glow!

Have you ever wondered the difference between waxing vs threading your brows? 🤔

Threading is more precise –and the best way to get your brows a natural look –, while waxing is great for big areas (such as legs and armpits). 😮

Threading is the best way to pluck your brows because removes any size or type of hair, plus it is gentle on sensitive skin.

Today, September 30, 2021, marks the first National Day for Truth and Reconciliation in Canada. This day commemorates all those impacted by Canada’s residential school system – the children lost, survivors and their families, and their communities. 

Reconciliation is a shared responsibility and patient process to heal the relationships between Indigenous and non-Indigenous Canadians. It is a time for us to come together, and requires listening and uplifting Indigenous voices, acknowledging the painful legacy of residential schools and cultural oppression, and understanding the lasting impacts on Indigenous communities, not just today, but everyday. 

So what can we do to honour those who have been impacted by Canada’s residential school system?
🧡 Respectfully listen to the experiences of residential school survivors
🧡 Familiarize yourself with the 94 Calls to Action by the Truth and Reconciliation Commission and take action
🧡 Join the community in a moment of silence at 2:15pm
🧡 Buy and wear an orange shirt to show solidarity with Indigenous communities, ensuring proceeds go to Indigenous communities

As settlers, it is our responsibility to demand better of ourselves and our governments. 

– Xo Bombay

Here's a little fox eye tutorial that you have been asking for! Are you ready? 🤓

✨Straight your brow shape 
To create a straight brow line, we suggest you use a pomade rather than a pencil. When you're in the middle of your brow, start going slightly upwards to create an illusion of a lifted brow.

✨Contour your eye
The trick here is to use a light brown eyeshadow to give you a blurring. 

✨Do a winged liner 
Outline the wing with a liquid liner for a more dramatic effect.

✨Chose the right mascara 
Swiping the mascara wand to the side and out to further will help elongate your lashes and add an extra touch to your fox eye. 

Now you can join the fox eye trending you have been seeing everywhere. 😉
When you do, please tag us. We'd love to see how they turn out. 💖✨

Coming from a family of immigrants, Canada has afforded us many opportunities and privileges that have helped shape the way our lives are today, including the opportunity to launch Bombay Beauty Co, a brand that has allowed us to celebrate our heritage and work on something that we are passionate about every single day.

However, this is not the lived experience of all Canadians, especially Indigenous peoples, whose land we live, work, and benefit from.

This July 1st, not only should we be supporting Indigenous businesses, taking the time to re-learn Canada’s dark history, and reflecting on its recent actions, we should be uplifting Indigenous voices, educating others, and challenging the narrative where we can. 

Our mantra is LOVE, and as a cause that is very close to our heart, a portion of all @bombaybeautyco sales will go towards the Indian Residential School Survivors Society (IRSSS) throughout the month of July to support Indigenous families that have been impacted by the residential school system. 

And we hope you, too, can help us support the cause in whatever way you can.

24/7 support is available for anyone affected by the effects of residential schools at 1-800-721-0066 🖤

Which dosha are you? 👇🏻

Dosha’s are part of the holistic approach we take with our services at Bombay Brow and our all natural skin products from @bombaybeautyco 

The 3 doshas are Kapha, Pitta, and Vata: 

🌎 🌊 Kapha is based on earth and water. It can be described as steady, stable, and soft. Spring is known as kapha season, as many parts of the world slowly exit hibernation.

🔥🌊 Pitta dosha is known for being associated with a tenacious personality, based on fire and water. It’s commonly described as hot, sharp, and mobile. Summer is known as pitta season!

💨✨ Vata consists mostly of the two elements air and space and is generally described as cold, flowing, and spacious. Autumn typically represents vata for its cool, crisp days.

All of our services and products are designed to help you balance your dosha, and help you achieve a healthy and more balanced lifestyle. Book your appointment online today at the link in our bio!

What are your brow goals for the year? As we head into March, here’s some food for thought (no, pun intended) on achieving dreamy brows 

🍽️ A big part of growing those crush-worthy brows has to do with what you put inside your body, not just on the outside. Look for foods rich in biotin: eggs, avocados, salmon, and peanuts

🧴 Check food labels for sources of vitamin B and D. These vitamins help hair growth and can help combat the effects of any chemical-based makeup you wear 

🥤 A glass of water never hurt anyone, so be sure to hydrate. Drinking at least 8-10 glasses every day can help flush out toxins from your body, improve hair quality, and quicken growth.

Are you breaking out with acne around your #FaceMask? We’re seeing a recent trend in what’s called “maskne” (aka #acne caused by wearing face masks). 

#Maskne is usually caused by one of two things (or both): friction or stress. When we wear our masks for long periods of time, they create friction on our sensitive skin. This is why you’ll commonly find “maskne” on your face around where your mask or face shield sits. 

There are several ways to avoid or minimize the severity of any skin breakouts caused by long-term use of face masks. Here are some tips to avoid maskne:

𝗧𝗶𝗽 𝟭. Look at your mask material. 100% cotton allows your skin to breathe better 
𝗧𝗶𝗽 𝟮. Wash your reusable masks frequently
𝗧𝗶𝗽 𝟯. Be mindful of your skincare routine. Rose is a great natural anti-septic 
𝗧𝗶𝗽 𝟰. Rethink your makeup habits by ensuring your cleaning and moisturizing your skin at the end of the day
𝗧𝗶𝗽 𝟱. Reduce your stress by looking for ways to reduce your stress or calm your mind and body 

Check out our latest blog, 5 Tips to Prevent Maskne - and explore  these five tips and gives suggestions on how to prevent Maskne from recurring. Click the link in our bio to read.

. #challengeaccepted #womensupportingwomen #womensupportingwomeninbusiness  thanks to @rajkainth1 for thinking of our co-founder @ravymehroke in this #Instagramchallenge that spreads love and support to women around the globe seeking justice for what’s right.
.
We’ve researched this challenge and learned it began in Turkey after the death of Pinar Gultekin, who was murdered by her ex-boyfriend. Women began posting black and white photos of themselves due to the frustration of seeing obit photos of women (usually b&w).
.
The idea is that by posting a photo of you in b&w you are showing solidarity with them, demanding change and a voice to the voiceless. These women are your sisters. Bring them back to life by sharing their story as many men still disregard their worth and ours.
.
Instagram challenges often mutate over time, but We see the love and support for one another with this one. Even if ppl may not recognize it’s original meaning. Stand for your girlfriends and women across the globe. Include the hashtags when sharing your B&W photo:

#femicide.
#feminism.
#womenempoweringwomen.
#sisterhood.
#kadınaşiddetehayır.
#istanbulsözleşmesiyaşatır.
.

Many people think happiness lies in the next place, the next achievement, the next relationship — as if peace is waiting just around the corner, one life change away. 

But no matter where you go, there you are. 

You bring your thoughts, your emotions, your patterns, and your restlessness with you.

If you can’t find contentment within, no location will provide it. 

If you can’t appreciate being alive right here and now, you likely won’t appreciate it in some other time or place. 

If your mind is chaotic, even paradise will feel like a prison. 

Real peace is not found by running away or reaching some new destination — it’s found by turning inward, by learning to be fully present with yourself here and now, and by being in touch with the wonder of life in each moment. 

When you can be at ease within your own being, and fully present with life as it is in each moment, the whole world becomes your sanctuary 🙏💚

#beherenow #bewhereyouare #appreciateyourlife

God’s Love We Deliver is so grateful for the continued support of @bcefa! Their latest grant of $50,000 supports us in preparing and delivering Medically Tailored Meals to individuals in the New York area living with HIV/AIDS.
 
Community support is vital to our mission and reflected in the communities we serve. God’s Love originates from supporting individuals in NYC marginalized and stigmatized due to illness, as founder Ganga Stone demonstrated by delivering our first meal to her friend dying from HIV/AIDS at the height of the AIDS pandemic in New York City.
 
Broadway Cares supports organizations which provide services for people affected by HIV/AIDS and their families. Broadway Cares is helping us reach our goal of serving over 90,000 meals annually to individuals living with HIV/AIDS and their families.
 
We are grateful for the longstanding partnership we have with Broadway Cares, dating back over 30 years.

Join us this Sunday, May 18 for the 40th Annual AIDS Walk, presented by @viivhealthcare and @gmhc ❤️

This year’s walk is especially meaning as it comes during a major milestone: our 40th anniversary! Founded in 1985 at the height of the HIV/AIDS pandemic, God’s Love has been nourishing New Yorkers affected by the illness ever since.

Sign up to walk and support our team through donations at glwd.org/AidsWalk today!

Happy 40th Birthday to @godslovenyc! The block party on Weehawken Street with @heermancefarm Kitchen was a beautiful celebration of four decades of compassion, care, and community.

Since delivering their first meal by bike in 1985, God’s Love We Deliver has grown into a lifeline for New Yorkers living with serious illnesses-now providing millions of meals each year.

Here’s to 40 years of nourishing our neighbors, and to the incredible volunteers and supporters who make it all possible.

Grateful to join this milestone moment!

At God’s Love We Deliver, our work is powered by the dedicated staff who prepare meals, deliver nourishment, support clients, and bring compassion to every step of our client’s health journies.
 
This past Friday, we celebrated Staff Appreciation Day to recognize the dedication behind our mission: ensuring that no one faces illness alone or without nutritious food. From chefs to drivers, nutritionists to client services, philanthropy to facilities — every role makes a difference in delivering medically tailored meals and love to our fellow New Yorkers!
 
We took time to reflect on our commitment to excellence, dignity, and care — values that define God’s Love We Deliver every day! We look forward to nourishing New Yorkers for many years to come, and say thank you to all those who support our life affirming work ❤️ Special thanks to @slateny for hosting us!
 
📸 Photos by @rdemano 
 
#StaffAppreciation

If MFA isn't on, you're exposed.

Work-from-home setups come with unique cybersecurity and IT challenges

From insecure networks to personal devices, remote workers face risks that don’t exist in the office.

Here are some tips to help protect yourself if you work from home.

#Cybersecurity #IT #Infosec #WFH #Remotework

Cyber Insurance vs. Partnering with an MSSP

Cyber insurance helps you recover after an attack.
An MSSP helps you prevent one in the first place.

Both have value, but only one actively reduces your risk in real time.

#IT #Infosec #MSP #MSSP #Cybersecurity

Bitcoin ATM scams are on the rise

Scammers pose as government agents, tech support, even your boss — pressuring you to send money fast.

They walk you through using a Bitcoin ATM to transfer untraceable funds.

🚫 No legit organization will ever ask you to pay this way.

#Cybersecurity #Scam #IT #Infosec #Bitcoin

#Apple #Keyboard #Cybersecurity #IT #Infosec

Why is it always the intern?

But for real — it might seem harmless, but sharing confidential info in chat apps puts your business at serious risk.

Use secure channels and train your whole team. Not just the interns.

#Cybersecurity #IT #Data #Infosec #Slack #Teams

Before you kick off that weekend workout, careful downloading that new fitness app.

Recently, malicious apps have been posing as a tracker,  but they go beyond fitness. Typically, asking for access to your contacts, messages, and other sensitive data they don't need.

Location might make sense, but your contact list doesn’t.

Stay smart. Stay secure.

Back at the NXT Conclave 2025, I had the honour of joining 20 visionary global leaders to speak on something deeply close to my heart, emotional and mental well-being. 🇮🇳

It felt historic to represent India with tools that aren’t new or foreign, but timeless and rooted.

 And it was even more special because our honourable PM Shri Narendra Modi Ji has been one of the first global leaders to give lifestyle and preventive health the stage it deserves.

From yoga to sunlight, from stillness to service, India’s always had these answers.

Here’s how you can start bringing them into your day:
☀️ Start with nature. Wake up, step into natural light, walk barefoot, breathe deeply, these aren’t trends, they’re time-tested tools.
 🧘🏽 Build inner peace. Through prayer, pranayama, or Surya Namaskar, whatever helps you go inward.
 🌀 Reframe stress. It’s not always a threat; it’s often a challenge, inviting growth.
 📚 Keep learning. Stay open, stay humble, wisdom often comes from unexpected places.
 🤝 Connect and give. Whether through volunteering or simple kindness, acts of service are powerful medicine.
 🎧 Guard your mind. Just like food, what you feed your mind matters; choose content that aligns with your values.
 🙏🏽 Gratitude always. Especially on tough days. It shifts perspective, softens the heart, and brings clarity.

This isn’t about a perfect routine. It’s about returning to what’s always worked.
 Small, consistent steps that help you evolve, mentally, emotionally, and spiritually.
Heal in India. Made in India. Rooted in India.

We’ve also compiled a comprehensive booklet the Bharat Lifestyle Plan that was presented to our honourable Prime Minister for all of you to see, download, learn, share and implement in your lives.

Download your copy (available in Hindi, English, Marathi, Gujarati) from the link in bio.

There are no words that can truly capture the weight of what our brave soldiers endure in the line of duty.

Every member of #TeamLuke bows in honour and gratitude to the brave soldiers who sacrificed their lives, to the officers and comrades who stood by them with support and strength, and to their grieving families whose silent sacrifices are no less heroic.

These heroes were not just soldiers, they were our sons, our fathers, our brothers, and our friends. They carried with them dreams, hopes, and an unwavering commitment to the safety of every single one of us.

They gave their lives for the peace we often take for granted, standing guard in the face of danger, knowing that each moment could be their last. And yet, they did it without hesitation, with unmatched courage, strength, and selflessness. Their sacrifices are beyond measure, and their bravery is a light that will forever guide us.

As we remember them today, I can’t help but feel an overwhelming sense of gratitude and sorrow. Gratitude for their immense sacrifice, and sorrow for the lives they could have lived but didn’t.

Rest in peace, heroes. Your legacy is not just in the stories we tell, but in the freedom we live. Your sacrifice will never be forgotten. You are forever etched in our hearts and minds, and we will continue to carry your spirit with us in every step we take, every victory we achieve, and every peaceful moment we get to experience.

We owe it all to you. 🙏🇮🇳💔

Jai Hind, Jai Bharat. 🇮🇳

Most people don’t expect me to talk about music 🎶 when it comes to healing.

But I’ve witnessed firsthand how sound, when used intentionally, can become a powerful tool in one’s healing journey. 🌿

In the powerful equation of healing, every element—medicine 💊, nutrition 🥦, movement 🏃‍♂️, sleep 😴, breathwork 🌬️, & emotional well-being 💖—plays an important part. 

But one powerful tool that often gets overlooked is sound or music.

You feel tired all the time.
Your energy dips for no reason.
You’ve checked your bloodwork.
Your hemoglobin is normal.
Your doctor says things look fine.

But your hair is falling.
Your nails are brittle.
Your skin looks dull.
You’re foggy. You’re restless. 

You’re not imagining it.
There’s something deeper going on.

Have you looked at your ferritin levels?
Because we’ve seen this with so many clients, the problem isn’t always in the obvious markers.
It’s in the reserves.

Ferritin is your iron bank.
Hemoglobin can look perfect while ferritin is quietly running on empty.
This is what we call iron deficiency without anemia (IDWA), which is an early red flag.

This is why a holistic approach matters.
Because health isn’t just about fixing the obvious.
It’s about understanding the systems underneath the symptoms.

Medicine is powerful, and always take what your doctor prescribes.
But pair it with a lifestyle plan:
→ Check your nutrition
→ Understand absorption
→ Address gut health
→ Work on rest and recovery
→ And always recheck.

Sometimes the answer is that simple.
And sometimes it takes zooming out, not digging deeper.

That’s the beauty of integrative and lifestyle medicine — it doesn’t replace, it complements.

.

A timeless moment in sports history.

reminder that there is always good in the world, and that even in the
darkest of times, there is always light.

As most people on social media, I tend to compare myself to others, feeling like I am never enough, there is always someone with bigger campaigns, bigger covers, bigger following:

Thank you for allowing me to share my journey with you, for all your support and for always making me want to strive further ✨

We tried that viral rice paper hack for our dim sum fave, cheung fun 🧐

The verdict? It’s def a lot chewier than traditional steamed rice noodle rolls — but not bad in a pinch and SO easy! 4/5 ngl 🤷🏻‍♀️

RECIPE 👇🏽
1 lb. shrimp
Rice paper
Omsom Lemongrass BBQ Sauce
2 stalks of scallions, sliced
Dipping sauce: 1 part soy sauce, 3 parts water, 1 part sugar, 1 part oil

1️⃣ Marinate shrimp in the Omsom sauce + half your sliced scallions.
2️⃣ Wet rice paper quickly in warm water to soften. Lay 3 shrimp onto rice paper and roll into tight rolls. Set on a lightly oiled plate.
3️⃣ Steam rice paper rolls under lightly boiling water for 2-3 minutes until shrimp is opaque + cooked through. 
4️⃣ Serve with dipping sauce!

Spring is well and truly here! 🌸 🐣 🌤️
But what does the Spring mean for our skin, and what do you need to be especially careful of when it comes to skincare?

Spring is the season when our skin is at its driest and most unstable. It has a weakened skin barrier function (winter has pushed it to its limits), so is less able to retain as much moisture and protect itself from the environment, including allergens like pollen. As the weather gets warmer and humidity levels increase, our skin has to learn to adapt yet again.

So what can we do to support our Spring skin? 🤔
By re-balancing the skin we can help it to retain moisture and build up its resilience to the changing climate and environment.

✨ Cleanse skin well, morning and night if you can
✨ Gently exfoliate once a week (our homemade scrub is perfectly gentle for this!)
✨ Moisturise more! Not just your face, but arms, legs and all the parts that have been hiding under a snuggly jumper 😉 
✨ Don’t forget your SPF! Choose one that protects agains UVA and B, and make sure you use it daily (even on cloudy days!) ⛅

Your skin produces more sebum in the warmer months, so you may find that your winter moisturiser feels a little too heavy. If so, consider choosing a lighter moisturiser that will reduce any skin-overload.
And most importantly, enjoy the sunshine and fresh air! ☺️ 💖

Proud to present part 1 of my Alpine capsule collection which I designed with @kiton .
Titled „Night and Day“ these exclusive garments were handmade in Naples by @kiton’s master tailors using the very finest of cashmere fabrics. My inspiration for this collection was a throwback to the glory days of alpine sports when men wore blazers and ties proudly as they navigated steep glaciers and traversed crevases on some of the most hostile and challenging terrain. Images of handsome bronzed European men in the 1970’s and 1980’s blazing down the slopes of St Moritz dressed like they were on the way to a formal dinner has always inspired me. Those who know me well are aware of my love for luxury fabrics and my penchant for the finest of tailoring. This next step in my career has been a wonderful experience and to have had the opportunity to design with the masters of Italian style @kiton has been a dream come true. Travelling to Naples last summer to select the fabrics and work on designs with the Paone family was an experience I will never forget. To see the teams of artisans hand stitching each garment step by step is simply breathtaking. Bravo @kiton . My mission is to bring timeless elegance back to the slopes and we are only starting. “SAINT MORITZ” a short movie by Tony Kelly
 
For years I have been fascinated by high alpine monasteries and churches of religious orders that were the early settlers in the mountains. There is a James Bond like mystique attached to these incredible outposts that have offered shelter and warmth to many weary travellers for centuries. Even Napoleon himself was given two glasses of wine and some bread by the monks of the Great Saint Bernard hospice when he arrived there in 1800. For many, the most symbolic aspect of a mountain is the peak because it is believed that it is closest to heaven or other religious realms which drew these brave men to the Alpine. I wanted to create a series of heroic portraits to celebrate the men and women of the cloth whose lives are devoted to their faith and often in today’s lightning fast society are forgotten. Inspired by historical images I found of nuns skiing in the Scandinavian mountains and paintings of monks on skis at the St Bernard pass I have created a series of images that holds a special place in my heart.  Shot in my beloved St Moritz on a picture perfect day with blue skies and a foot of fresh snow. Presenting my latest fine art limited edition... “SAINT MORITZ”
For years I have been fascinated by high alpine monasteries and churches of religious orders that were the early settlers in the mountains. There is a James Bond like mystique attached to these incredible outposts that have offered shelter and warmth to many  weary travellers for centuries. Even Napoleon himself was given two glasses of wine and some bread by the monks of the Great Saint Bernard hospice when he arrived there in 1800. For many, the most symbolic aspect of a mountain is the peak because it is believed that it is closest to heaven or other religious realms which drew these brave men to the Alpine. I wanted to create a series of heroic portraits to celebrate the men and women of the cloth whose lives are devoted to their faith and often in today’s lightning fast society are forgotten. Inspired by historical images I found of nuns skiing in the Scandinavian mountains and paintings of monks on skis at the St Bernard pass I have created a series of images that holds a special place in my heart. 
This first piece from the series is produced in three sizes and was of course shot in my beloved St Moritz. A picture perfect day with blue skys and a foot of fresh snow gave me the canvas I had been waiting for! To collect or learn more click link in bio or contact art@tonykellyworld.com

“As we walked through Camp Tel Yehudah, a Young Judaea teen leadership summer camp in Barryville, New York where she worked in 2019 and 2022, there was Gili in her old room with the world map and desk she brought. Christmas time is here, and it's the season of giving! 🎁 But having the right strategy is important. Did you know you can make substantial, tax-free gifts to loved ones by using strategic gifting? Here’s how:

1️⃣ Annual Exclusion: Gift up to $18,000 per person per year with no gift tax. 
2️⃣ Lifetime Exemption: Use up to $13.61 million of lifetime exemptions to transfer wealth tax-free. 
3️⃣ Split Gifts: Married? Double up to give $36,000 per recipient if you're a married couple. 
4️⃣ Spread It Out: Consider spreading out your gift over multiple years to stay under the $18,000 per year limit. 
5️⃣ Direct Support: Payments for education or medical expenses go untaxed if paid directly to educational institutions or medical providers!

Estate planning helps you give thoughtfully, maximizing what you're able to leave behind for your loved ones. 📜 ✨

...

¡Llegó la época navideña y es la temporada de dar! 🎁 Pero es importante tener la estrategia correcta. ¿Sabías que puedes hacer obsequios sustanciales libres de impuestos a tus seres queridos mediante el uso de obsequios estratégicos? Aquí te contamos cómo:

1️⃣ Exclusión anual: obsequia hasta $18,000 por persona por año sin impuestos sobre donaciones.
2️⃣ Exención de por vida: usa hasta $13.61 millones de exenciones de por vida para transferir riqueza libre de impuestos.
3️⃣ Donaciones divididas: ¿Estás casado? Duplica la donación para dar $36,000 por destinatario si estás casado.
4️⃣ Distribuye tu donación: considera distribuirla en varios años para mantenerte por debajo del límite de $18,000 por año.
5️⃣ Apoyo directo: ¡Los pagos por educación o gastos médicos no están sujetos a impuestos si se pagan directamente a instituciones educativas o proveedores médicos!

La planificación patrimonial le ayuda a donar de manera considerada, maximizando lo que puede dejar para sus seres queridos. 📜 ✨

@bretnowell led us through an exercise that opened our minds in a whole new way. It was amazing, it was exhausting, it was life changing. In life, we all carry our own rocks—symbolizing the burdens, responsibilities, and challenges we face. Carrying the rock represents our personal strength, perseverance, and the weight of our unique journeys. Every step taken with that rock is a testament to our resilience and determination. But there’s another aspect: passing the rock. When we share our burdens, seek help, or offer support, we lighten the load for ourselves and others. Passing the rock is about community, connection, and the strength found in unity. It reminds us that while we each have our struggles, we don’t have to face them alone. So whether you’re carrying the rock or passing it, remember that both are acts of courage and strength. Embrace the journey and lean on those around you. Together, we are stronger. 💪🪨 #StrengthInUnity #CarryTheRock #PassTheRock

Key takeaway lessons below 👇🏼 I believe this is true for any creative process. 
We all have an inner mother. Even if you have trauma. That person who knows what’s best for you is inside you. Making you continue. Pushing you . Believing in you where others have not. Things I impatiently forgot:
🔑 I made the mistake of not grounding myself with clear direction.
Get your vision clear for what you’re going to do. MAKE A CLEAR PLAN 
👁️ 🌞 👁️ 
🔑 I made the mistake of tripping out and falling back in to negative self talk. Anytime I really want the outcome to please someone other than me, it’s a vulnerable area where my insecurities cloud my judgement. I’m working on this, I know the solution is to quiet the inner critic and HAVE FAITH IN MYSELF 🙏🩷 IF IT DOESNT WORK OUT. LEARN. GROW. TRY AGAIN. 

🔑 🛠️ USE SHORTCUTS (especially if you’re newer like me 😮‍💨)
I’ve been a foolish snob about them until now.  I made the mistake of not allowing myself to take a few shortcuts that would’ve saved so much time! I’ve decided that I want to work towards more freehand art without these tools, but each day I’ll get better.  If a subject is mirrored from one side to the other, it’s way less forgiving and quite challenging to get it perfectly symmetrical on each side. I learned that even some of the old masters used these tools. I wish I would’ve from the start 😵‍💫
RENDER in photoshop etc beforehand if you didn’t do a photo shoot or it’s in your head. This is a test so you can see proportions and what paint colors to use 🎨 
GRIDS to scale the subject . It’s so easy to think you can eyeball it. But this is the closest thing to guarantee it.
I’ve read some artists use projectors , I haven’t but I might try it out now😅 I mean who cares? It’s still your concept, your hand creating the strokes. 
RULERS, STENCILS, ETC. All useful 🙌 

I hope this helps someone like me :)(:
Please comment any keys 🔑 you’ve discovered for community value 🙏😃 #oilpainter #oilportrait #femaleartist

#designershoes 

📍The real real @therealreal has authenticated items for crazy cheap all throughout the year!!
I do two things: heart my favorites and come back to check up on prices later.
Search ultra refined with sizes and item categories wanted, then ideal price range (best deals are in midrange for each category). I snagged a new condition burberry trench for $130 last season. Retail $2590. The great thing about buying authentic is the items are truly better quality than dupes so they last and you can reconsign them so easily if you get tired of the style! But classics are great 👌🏽 These shoes were $129.
📍 FWRD  @fwrd and other luxury sites: search sales from price low to high with your sizes to find designer goods for less, the recommended items are usually NOT the best deals.
📍If you wear a popular size don’t wait until end of the season clearance, shop sales mid season and watch for discount codes!
📍Buying designer items and jewelry in Italy or their country of origin can save you up to 30%, sometimes more.
Research what the local commodities are prior to traveling.
📍I like to mix inexpensive cotton basics and trendy items with designer to stretch things more. Classy items can elevate the WHOLE look. 
📍When a piece is really unique or limited I get it if I love it because it’s more likely to retain its value. Additionally, some things I see I know I want to pass down through generations. These items can sometimes be sold for higher than their original retail (Hermes etc) but be careful with this one because it’s easy to say you’re “investing” when it’s unlikely that you will see a return on the item lol and you’re having fun 😅
📍 Rental memberships for medium to high quality apparel and accessories are SUPER EASY to handle. I do RTR but I’ve heard great things about other sites like Vivrelle @vivrelle . I got off the plane in Paro, Bhutan and upon first glance of the massive portrait of His Majesty the King’s family portrait, I knew I was in a mystical place.  The epic beauty of this airport which reads more like a temple was just an introduction to an entire country’s emphasis on material beauty signifying devotion to God. 

And after a decade of dreaming of this perfect country whose spirituality is at the forefront of its existence, I was so excited to visit the parliamentary Zhongs which are always 3/4 monastery, where government officials work alongside monks.  To meet the team and learn about the upcoming Gelephu Mindfullness City @gmcbhutan , where @kingjigmekhesar 
is planning a futuristic city where ethical capitalism can co-exist with nature. 

I even found some equanimous perfection in a monk answering his cell phone in the middle of my blessing ceremony or even people making tik tok’s at the temple. The serenity of a country without billboards, traffic lights, or noise pollution made me realize the chaos we have all become accustomed to.  And on the flipside humanity cannot live without its transgressions.  You can go through religious ceremony repeatedly but still be devoid of spiritual grace.  So grateful for this heart mind and soul opening experience!  Thank you BHUTAN

*My Nephew NICOLAI*
I spent this fall day walking around my beloved hometown with my nephew, taking photos with my Hasselblad. 
We are an eyewear family.  When my father left his toy business after fleeing Iran in the late 70’s, he came to LA where an acquaintance was in the eyewear business. That world raised us.  One day I would be in his office putting glasses in bags, the next day Ol’ Dirty Bastard was in my living room modeling for my brother’s line while I was wearing the kid’s collection.  All I have is love for my family and the city that took us in.  You can be whoever you want to be in LA.

If you’re looking for another passport, Portugal offers the highest ROI for Indians compared to any other citizenship program in the world…

While the Indian passport gives you visa free access to about 60 countries, the Portugal passport gives you 188 countries visa free, including US, Canada, UK and the whole of Europe.

To be eligible, you have to visit Portugal for just 7 days per year, and maintain an investment in their country for 5 years, on which you get about 12% per annum, and I’ll explain how.

The citizenship of UK costs about Rs 21 crores (GBP 2 million), of Malta costs over Rs 6 crores (EUR 700k+), but for Portugal it costs just about Rs 3 crores (EUR 350k)

You can invest this amount in real estate in Portugal, where since 2015, properties have appreciated by 8-10% annually, while giving 4-7% rental yields, thus giving 12% annual returns.

A tech company founder from Bangalore invested about Rs 4.5 crores (EUR 500k) in a Lisbon apartment five years ago - the property appreciated by 47%, generated rental income, AND he used Portugal as his European headquarters, expanding his business across the EU.

And here’s a sweetener… Portugal follows the “Non-Habitual Resident” tax program - you pay just 20% flat tax rate on professional income and potentially zero tax on foreign-source income for 10 years.

There’s a lot more nuance to this. Do it in consultation with a professional.

While most people take investing advice from Warren Buffett... I like referring to his advice on hiring...

He says there are only three things you should look out for while hiring people -

1/ Integrity
2/ Intelligence
3/ Energy

If they don’t have the first one, the other two will kill you.

Now, most interviews test number two and three - as both intelligence and energy can be perceived and felt from the resume, and their demeanour.

It’s testing the integrity that takes the most amount of effort...

To do this, you need to ask them two questions:

1/ Tell me about a time when upholding your principles cost you something valuable... and 

2/ Describe a situation where you made a significant mistake at work. How did you handle it?

The biggest red flags in an answer would be if they blame the failure on the team and can’t take ownership... or even if they have no failure story to share, or give non specific vague answers.

Someone who gives you a weakness that is actually a strength is the biggest bullcrapper on the planet because you want someone who can be real and own up to their genuine shortcomings.

Combine the above with two solid references of people you can speak with and check the above... It could be superiors, peers, but someone of credibility who can validate it.

You could ask the references to rate the candidate’s trustworthiness on a scale of 1 to 10, and if they give him an 8 or 9, ask why they deducted a point and what would make them worthy of a full 10.

What’s the Cost of Living for a Nuclear Family in Toronto? 

How much money would you need if you want to move to Toronto with your family — that is, spouse and a young child — and lead a decent life?

-	Rentals will cost you about Rs 2.5 lakhs monthly (CAD 3500 – 4000), for a 2-bedroom apartment in a decent neighborhood like North York, Etobicoke, or Mississauga.

-	Groceries would add up to another Rs 75k (CAD 1250).

-	Transportation — whether it’s public transport (TTC) or a personal car lease plus insurance — would cost another Rs 50k (CAD 750).

-	Childcare can easily cost Rs 1 lakh (CAD 1500–2000) per month, if both parents are working.

-	Eating out, entertainment and lifestyle expenses: keep aside about Rs 1 lakh (CAD 1750).

-	Insurance, contingencies, medicals (even with OHIP in place): another Rs 50k (CAD 750).

Which means at least Rs 6 lakhs (roughly CAD 10,000) per month.

If your earning in Toronto is going to be less than CAD 120,000 post tax annually, you may be better off staying in India and earning Rs 2.5 lakhs per month instead.

This means, try and get a pre-tax salary package of no less than CAD 150,000 per annum for a half decent life.

Now, people also live in Toronto for easily 30% lesser than the above figures, but that’s with really cutting corners and being harsh on your spends.

This is how I’m seeing a few people double their pay in their 30s…

It comes with some risk but the pay off is totally worth it.

The concept of a Mini Retirement is increasingly becoming popular…
 
Increasingly, a number of people in their 30s are frustrated that their jobs keep them so busy with such administrative and repetitive work that even if they want to learn new skills to stay relevant, there is absolutely no time with work meetings, travel to the office, family commitments and more…
 
And this is even more frustrating when people realize that their juniors are switching companies, taking bigger promotions, and their experience is rusting their ability to be hired elsewhere…
 
Which is why the concept of a mini retirement is picking up where people decide to take a break from work for around 12 months…
 
Which would mean building up a fund to last you a year of expenses, moving to a cheaper destination or a tier 2 city, and then spending the next six months on just learning new skills like AI, Blockchain, or in whatever domain you want to upskill in…

And then coming back to applying to newer roles in the latter half, giving yourself one year to upskill and restart your career…
 
Some people are also taking up part time freelancing gigs during this period which helps them stay in the zone of working about 10 hours a week, while keeping the remaining time free to learn.
 
Think it’s a low cost self taught MBA break because even MBA colleges are not being able to keep up with new skills in today’s time.
 
These breaks are also being called “Mini Retirements” on the resume instead of sabbaticals, which when asked about during an interview, gives you an opportunity to show how you are invested in learning even when your colleagues are just doing the old things.
 
Companies like Adobe, Linkedin and AirBnB also have extended leave programs that help retain talent and reduce burnout.
 
The stigma attached to it is definitely going away.

I want to tell you something that happened with me yesterday…

I was checking into a hotel in New York… and saw that the person checking us in at the property was of brown descent…

Generally, over a chat I appreciated his swift assistance with the process, and over the conversation asked him where he was from…

He stopped for a few seconds and said Gujarat…

I could tell from the way he spoke that he was from across the border in Pakistan… and chose to say Gujarat because its a safe word that gives the impression that one is from India while few people know that there is a city called Gujarat in Pakistan.

And I’ve seen this time and again not just in the US, but in Canada, UK, Europe… no matter where you go…

People from Pakistan seem so embarrassed of their country often times that they present themselves as Indians…

You’ll see this also in the fact that most of the Indian restaurants being run in the UK are being run by Pakistanis but they will call it an Indian Restaurant and not Pakistani.

So it’s not something they’ll say to people who are Indian…

It’s often clear that a lot of Pakistanis abroad in Western economies are embarrassed of not just how their government behaves but also how it is perceived globally.

I have absolutely no hate for civilians and wish the well to all, but I also want to take this as an opportunity to say that the Indian brand has helped a lot of people across the border actually find a livelihood in other countries, and they should be mindful of how they behave with our country.

My condolences to everyone from India who lost their lives in the war, and a reminder to the world…

That its always Jai Hind before anything else.

After Analogue Paneer… the next product you’ll see a lot of adulteration and fakes are in your coffee…

In the past 5 years, coffee prices have gone up from $1000 a tonne to $5000 a tonne.

It’s a 5X increase in 5 years, and a 3X in the past 3 years…

It’s all because the demand for coffee around the world has gone so up north, that people who never cared about it earlier are now into collecting coffees, and enjoying unique brews multiple times a day…

This is fuelled with constantly dropping yields…

Two if the largest suppliers in the world are Brazil and Vietnam, and they’re both seeing a poor crop season.

There is a high chance that these prices may remain unpredictable for another couple of years… so coffee companies in India and around the world are facing a very tough time with increasing costs, and pressure to increase price which they feel the market will not accept…

I predict that your Instant Coffee brands will soon change their composition to add a lot more chicory powder, which is the root of a plant, roasted and mixed into coffee blends…

As for the cafés you go to, if they are really into serving the best single origin coffees, their prices should go up by about 20%… so a Rs 300 cup may now cost closer to Rs 400

Also, currently, the instant coffee brands have 70% actual coffee and the balance is chicory, so remember to check the ingredients to see what you’re really drinking.

Different US Cities and Their Respective Industry Focus
 
Cities in the US are so different in culture from each other that if you want to do business with US clients, you have to understand what they would prioritize…
 
For example, New York does not care about startups, what it cares about is finance, media and fashion. If you’re in NY, the way to win is to understand global financial markets and be extremely fashionable to fit in… (It has seen 85% growth in fintech investments over the past 3 years)
 
Boston, on the other hand, is quite the opposite. It’s all about building businesses that are built on long term vision, patient capital, and years of research like in Biotechnology and in AI. To win here, you have to belong to a top educational institute… (They’ve had over USD 8 Bn invested in Biotech just last year)
 
While San Francisco would be known as the Startup Capital, Austin is now the fastest growing tech hub with companies like Tesla and Oracle moving here, and new tech founders are willing to come here instead. They all prioritize growth over profitability.
 
By comparison, Chicago startups reach profitability much faster and are more profit conscious.
 
LA’s focus is on media tech and gaming, clearly with its links to Hollywood. If you’re building something in the creator economy, this is where you come.
 
And if you wish to build in Crypto or focus on the Latin American market, you come down and build in Miami.
 
As for Seattle, go there is you work in Microsoft or Amazon. There is absolutely no other reason to be there.

As the face of this year’s Met Gala, model #ChristianLatchman personified the essence of Superfine: Tailoring Black Style—a tribute to the legacy of Black dandyism. Celebrity makeup artist @nicolewittman reveals how she prepped his skin with iS Clinical to bring this vision to life:

"This moment was about so much more than glam. It was about presence, strength, and graciousness. From the very start, I knew the skin had to lead the way. The goal wasn’t to cover, but to enhance — letting Christian’s natural radiance, confidence, and story shine through. Skincare was the star of this look. Every product was carefully chosen to nourish, calm, and elevate his skin, allowing it to speak for itself. Because today wasn’t about seeing makeup — it was about seeing Christian. What a privilege to be part of a moment where beauty meets meaning.

Refresher: Responsive desire emerges in response to pleasure or arousal, whereas spontaneous desire emerges in anticipation of pleasure or arousal. 

Libido is not a static experience. It’s normal for it to ebb, flow, and fluctuate.

These are just a few examples of the many ways in which libido can change over time. If you experience libido changes, please know that’s to be expected over time. Caveat: this won’t resonate for everyone *and* we see this dynamic in couples therapy often.

“Our collective voices really matter. 

We have to have a diversity of community so they can reflect back on us, so we’re not in delusion…

It’s very easy today to get into reality tunnels with social media or whatnot, where you’re just kind of seeing one thing, or just what you want to see, and it’s reaffirming a particular viewpoint that is gonna feel extremely real because that’s all you’re seeing and hearing and being validated on. 

And it’s tricky because there’s not even a shared objective truth on certain regards. 

But not that psychedelics are a panacea, but at a certain dose, there’s nowhere to run, and you face what you face, and that’s, there can be some real work.”

Have you seen the documentary?

🌲🔊 One of my favorite parts of the creative process is recording sounds in nature—birds, wind, water, footsteps—and bringing them back into the studio as source material.

There’s something incredible about reconnecting with nature through sound… it grounds you, opens you up, and reminds you that music is everywhere if you listen closely. 🎶🌿

If you’re heading out on a nature walk, I highly recommend taking a moment to really listen—you might just find a rhythm, a melody, or even a moment of stillness that stays with you long after. 🎧
